# 1Ô∏è‚É£ Create Repository in GitHub

Using

## GitHub

![Image](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-29762/images/help/repository/repo-create-global-nav-update.png)

![Image](https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-80496/images/help/repository/sample-issue-form.png)

![Image](https://i.sstatic.net/Lq6yF.png)

![Image](https://imgs.kloudle.com/academy/how-to-update-public-repository-to-private-in-github/1673703712-repository-settings.png)

### Steps:

1. Login to GitHub
2. Click **New Repository**
3. Name:

   ```
   mgm-datalake-databricks-folder
   ```
4. Choose Private
5. Click Create

Now repo is ready.

