# 2Ô∏è‚É£ Generate Personal Access Token (PAT)

![Image](https://docs.catalyst.zoho.com/images/tutorials/githubbot/catalyst_gitbot_access_token_2.webp)

![Image](https://cdn.document360.io/3d44af5c-3f49-4ca5-b152-10836a885c13/Images/Documentation/Screen%20Shot%202023-03-27%20at%2011.56.53%20AM.png)

![Image](https://roadie.io/content/docs/integrations/github-token/public-repos-only.webp)

![Image](https://itknowledgeexchange.techtarget.com/coffee-talk/files/2021/08/github-support-password-authentication-removed-1.gif)

### Steps:

1. GitHub ‚Üí Settings
2. Developer Settings
3. Personal Access Token
4. Generate new token (classic)
5. Select:

   * repo
6. Copy token (save safely)

You will use this in Databricks.

---

# 3Ô∏è‚É£ Configure Git Integration in Databricks

Inside

## Azure Databricks

![Image](https://i.sstatic.net/H8p0X.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/link-github-account-in-databricks-84d9bb46388cb43b8283939751b4edd8.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-folder-ui1-1314c0b409b264609ca019dc28e81d54.png)

![Image](https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize%3Afit%3A1400/1%2AfHFWDPqW9Nr2FeWACSiGBQ.png)

### Steps:

1. Click your profile icon (top right)
2. Go to **User Settings**
3. Click **Git Integration**
4. Select:

   * Provider: GitHub
5. Paste PAT
6. Save

Now Databricks can talk to GitHub.

---

# 4Ô∏è‚É£ Create Git Folder (Repos)

This matches your screenshot exactly.

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-folder-ui1-1314c0b409b264609ca019dc28e81d54.png)

![Image](https://www.databricks.com/sites/default/files/2023-03/databricks-repos-02.svg?v=1678235630)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-dialog-new-branch-bdeefe3585ef2e47f9f12a235ea6bea4.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-repos-switch-branch-dialog-460305cff76bbe733ca156d5a1169297.png)

### Steps:

1. Go to:

   ```
   Workspace ‚Üí Home
   ```
2. Click **Create**
3. Select **Git Folder**
4. Paste GitHub repo URL
5. Select branch:

   ```
   main
   ```
6. Click Create

Now structure becomes:

```
Workspace
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Repos
       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ your_email
            ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ mgm-datalake-databricks-folder
```

Same like your image.

