# 5Ô∏è‚É£ Create develop Branch

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-repos-switch-branch-dialog-460305cff76bbe733ca156d5a1169297.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-folder-ui1-1314c0b409b264609ca019dc28e81d54.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-ops-3-a8eb75bfd112e06ca239db4651cf34ac.gif)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-commit-push-3e3acc438be0b1b47c7a4540f5cca854.png)

### Steps:

1. Open repo folder
2. Click branch dropdown (main)
3. Click **Create branch**
4. Name:

   ```
   develop
   ```
5. Create from main

Now you have:

```
main
develop
```

Exactly like your screenshot.

