# 6Ô∏è‚É£ Create Notebook Inside Repo

‚ö† Important: Must create notebook inside Git folder.

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/git-folder-ui1-1314c0b409b264609ca019dc28e81d54.png)

![Image](https://docs.databricks.com/aws/en/assets/images/job-list-dialog-38a5e628c5e1c85b491970b5590399f4.png)

![Image](https://www.databricks.com/sites/default/files/2023-03/databricks-repos-02.svg?v=1678235630)

![Image](https://www.databricks.com/sites/default/files/2023-03/repos-graphic.png?v=1679432905)

Steps:

1. Inside repo folder
2. Click **Create ‚Üí Notebook**
3. Name:

   ```
   bronze_to_silver
   ```
4. Language: Python

Now notebook is Git-tracked.

